The country’s Cabinet Secretary for Tourism, however, admits 2020 is as good as lost. SABC correspondent Sarah Kimani speaks about the financial woes brought on by COVID-19 in the country.

Kenya endorses Eliud Kipchoge as its tourism ambassador to help revive the sector.

Can sports help revive tourism? Kenya is hoping so. The East African nation has entered into an agreement with World Record marathon holder and Olympics champion Eliud Kipchoge to endorse Kenya as its tourism ambassador. The country has lost $800 million in tourism revenues since April 2020 with more than two million people who depend on the industry losing their livelihoods.     
--SABC--